6\u201372</small>}}\n{{tree chart/end}}\n\n==References and notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-hou|House of Normandy|||||name=*[[dynasty|Royal House]]*}}\n|-\n{{S-new}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Dynasty|Ruling House]] of the [[Duchy of Normandy]]|years= 911&ndash;1154}}\n{{S-aft|rows=2|after=[[House of Plantagenet]]}}\n|-\n{{S-bef|before=[[House of Wessex]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Dynasty|Ruling House]] of the [[Kingdom of England]]|years=1066&ndash;1154}}\n|-\n{{S-bef|before=[[House of Estridsen]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Dynasty|Ruling House]] of the [[County of Flanders]]|years=1127&ndash;1128}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[House of Alsace]]}}\n|-\n{{S-new}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Dynasty|Ruling House]] of the [[Eu, Seine-Maritime|County of Eu]]|years=996&ndash;1246}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[House of Lusignan]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Royal houses of Europe}}\n{{Kingdom of England}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dynasty, Norman}}\n[[Category:House of Normandy|Normandy]]\n[[Category:Viking Age in France]]\n[[Category:French noble families]]\n[[Category:English royal houses|Normandy]]\n[[Category:Royal houses of the County of Flanders|Normandy]]\n\n\n{{Normandy-stub}}\n{{UK-royal-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=October 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox noble house\n|surname          = House of Normandy\n|type             = <!-- Royal house, noble house, etc. -->\n|native_name      = \n|native_name_lang = \n|other_name       = \n|coat of arms     = Arms of William the Conqueror (1066-1087).svg\n|image_size       = 140px\n|alt              = \n|caption          = Arms of the duchy of Normandy<ref group=nb>The House of Normandy became extinct before the age of heraldry.</ref>\n|country          = France, England\n|estates          = Normandy, England, Flanders\n|parent house     = \n|titles           = \n*[[Count of Rouen]]\n*[[Duke of Normandy]]\n*[[King of England]]\n*[[Count of Flanders]]\n|styles           = \n|founded          = 911\n|founder          = [[Rollo]]\n|final ruler      = [[Henry I of England]]\n|current head     = \n|dissolution      = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}} -->\n|deposition       = 1135\n|cadet branches   = \nIllegitimate lines:\n*House of Devereux, [[Viscount Hereford|Viscounts Hereford]]\n*House of FitzRobert, [[Earls of Gloucester]]\n*House of Dunstanville, [[Earls of Cornwall]]\n|notes            = \n{{Reflist|group=nb}}\n}}\n\nThe '''House of Normandy''' is the usual designation for the family that were the [[counts of Rouen]], [[dukes of Normandy]] and [[kings of England]] which immediately followed the [[Norman conquest of England]] and lasted until the [[House of Plantagenet]] came to power in 1154. The house emerged from the union between the [[Viking]] [[Rollo]] (first ruler of the [[Duchy of Normandy]]) and [[Poppa of Bayeux]], a West Frankish noblewoman. [[William the Conqueror]] and his heirs down through 1135 were members of this dynasty. \n\nAfter that it was disputed between William's grandchildren, [[Matilda of England|Matilda]], whose husband  Geoffrey was the founder of the House of Plantagenet, and [[Stephen of England|Stephen]] of the [[House of Blois]] (or Blesevin dynasty).\n\nThe Norman counts of Rouen were:\n*[[Rollo]], 911\u2013927\n*[[William I, Duke of Normandy|William Longsword]], 927\u2013942\n\nThe Norman dukes of Normandy were:\n*[[Richard I, Duke of Normandy|Richard I]], 942\u2013996\n*[[Richard II, Duke of Normandy|Richard II]], 996\u20131027\n*[[Richard III, Duke of Normandy|Richard III]], 1026\u20131027\n*[[Robert I, Duke of Normandy|Robert I]], 1027\u20131035\n*[[William I of England|William]], 1035\u20131066 (became King of England as [[William the Conqueror]])\n\nThe Norman monarchs of England and Normandy were:\n*[[William the Conqueror]], 1066\u20131087\n*[[William II of England|William II]], 1087\u20131100 (not Duke of Normandy)\n*[[Robert Curthose|Robert II]], 1087\u20131106 (not King of England)\n*[[Henry I of England|Henry I]], 1100\u20131135; 1106\u20131135\n*[[William Adelin]], 1120 (not King of England)\n*[[Empress Matilda|Matilda]], 1135\u20131153<ref>Matilda's inheritance was usurped by her cousin Stephen of England in 1135. She recovered Normandy, but ruled in England only in 1141 as ''Lady of the English''. However, Matilda maintained her dynastic rights until she abdicated them in favour of her son [[Henry II of England]] in 1153 following the [[Treaty of Wallingford]].</ref>\n*[[Stephen, King of England|Stephen]] (non-[[Patrilineality#Agnatic succession|agnatic]]; a member of the [[Count of Blois|House of Blois]]), 1135\u20131154\n\nNorman Count of Flanders:\n*[[William Clito]] (r. 1127\u20131128), son of Robert Curthose, great-grandson of [[Baldwin V, Count of Flanders|Baldwin V]], designated by [[Louis VI of France]]\n\n==Family tree==\n{{main|English monarchs family tree}}\n''Counts of Rouen and Dukes of Normandy shown in bold.''\n\n{{tree chart/start}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | ROL | |ROL='''[[Rollo]]'''<br /><small>Count of Rouen 911\u2013927</small><br /><small>HOUSE OF NORMANDY</small>}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | |!}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | WIL | |WIL='''[[William I, Duke of Normandy|William<br /><small>\u2018Longsword\u2019</small>]]'''<br /><small>Count of Rouen 927\u2013942</small>}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | |!}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | RIC | |RIC='''[[Richard I, Duke of Normandy|Richard I<br /><small>\u2018the Fearless\u2019</small>]]'''<br /><small>Duke of Normandy 942\u2013996</small>}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | |)|-|-|-|v|-|-|-|v|-|-|-|v|-|-|-|.}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | RIC | | ROB | | MAU | | GEO | | WLL |RIC='''[[Richard II, Duke of Normandy|Richard II<br /><small>\u2018the Good\u2019</small>]]'''<br /><small>Duke of Normandy 996\u20131027</small>|ROB=[[Robert II (archbishop of Rouen)|Robert]]<br /><small>count of \u00c9vreux</small>|MAU=[[Mauger, Count of Corbeil|Mauger]]<br><small>\u221e Germain<br>countess of Corbeil</small>|GEO=[[Geoffrey, Count of Eu|Geoffrey]]<br /><small>count of Eu<small /><br />[[de Clare|CLARE]]|WLL=[[William I, Count of Eu|William I]]<br /><small>count of Eu<br />[[Counts of Eu|EU]]</small>}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | |,|-|-|-|(| | | |)|-|-|-|.| }}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | RIC | | ROB | | RCH | | RAL |RIC='''[[Richard III, Duke of Normandy|Richard III]]'''<br /><small>Duke of Normandy 1026-1027</small>|ROB='''[[Robert I, Duke of Normandy|Robert I<br /><small>\u2018the Magnificent\u2019</small>]]'''<br /><small>Duke of Normandy 1027\u201335</small>|RCH=[[Richard, Count of \u00c9vreux|Richard]]<br /><small>count of \u00c9vreux</small>|RAL=[[Ralph de Gac\u00e9|Ralph]]<br><small>lord of Gac\u00e9</small>}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | |!| | | |!| }}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | WIL | | WLM |WIL='''[[William I of England|William II <small>(King William I)</small><br />\u2018the Conqueror\u2019]]'''<br /><small>Duke of Normandy 1035\u201387<br />[[List of English monarchs|King of England]] 1066\u201387</small>|WLM=[[William, Count of \u00c9vreux|William]]<br /><small>count of \u00c9vreux</small>}}\n{{tree chart| |,|-|-|-|v|-|-|-|v|-|-|-|+|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|.| }}\n{{tree chart| ROB | | ADE | | RIC | | WIL | | | | | | HEN |ROB='''[[Robert Curthose|Robert II<br /><small>\u2018Curthose\u2019</small>]]'''<br /><small>Duke of Normandy 1087\u20131106</small>|RIC=[[Richard, son of William the Conqueror|Richard]]|WIL=[[William II of England|William II<br /><small>\u2018Rufus\u2019</small>]]<br /><small>King of England 1087\u2013110<br />''Ducal Regent 1096\u20131100''</small>|HEN='''[[Henry I of England|Henry I<br /><small>\u2018Beauclerc\u2019</small>]]'''<br /><small>King of England 1100\u201335<br />Duke of Normandy 1106\u201335</small>|ADE=[[Adela of Normandy|Adela]]<br /><small>\u221e [[Stephen II, Count of Blois|Stephen II,<br />Count of Blois]]</small>}}\n{{tree chart| |!| | | |!| | | | | | | |,|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|+|-|-|-|v|-|-|-|v|-|-|-|v|-|-|-|v|-|-|-|v|-|-|-|v|-|-|-